The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 October is 84,664 (9,758 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 October, there were 3,229 new confirmed cases (372.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 October, there were 2,398 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 35% (831 extra cases).
